  "name": "Ring Of Recalcitrant Wishes",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This band of interwoven gold and copper, traced with Aklo symbols, is topped with a gleaming, luminescent opal gently bleeding wisps of shadowstuff.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">3</span> command</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You attempt to make the ring cast an arcane <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.6dDtGIUerazSHIOu]{Wish}</em> spell. However, if the ring doesn't deem the wish to be sufficiently selfless, the wish isn't cast and the ring can't be activated for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>You are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.4D2KBtexWXa6oUMR]{Drained 3}, whether or not the ring refuses the wish.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Once the wish is cast, the Ring of Recalcitrant Wishes has no powers, though it is rumored that the wearer's death in an act of profound self-sacrifice restores the wish to the ring.</p>"
    },
